            <bug_when>2009-01-18 13:09:12 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>When using the Mousewheel in Tables to scroll the Table-content vertically, the bahaviour is not &#39;as usual&#39;. You can easily test this in the Demo-Browser (http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/demobrowser/#table~Table.html).

I tested this in Firefox 3.0.5

1. On Scroll-Down with the Mouse-Wheel (while Mousepointer is over the Table-Content), the table-content &#39;jumps&#39; directly to the bottom (top resp.)
2. Sometimes (i don&#39;t know why an when) it happens, that the scolling in ONE directions works &#39;a little bit&#39;, but a Wheel-Scroll to the other direction brings the table-content to the max-end (top resp. bottom)
</thetext>
